• Accounts Receivable (end of period) from the balance sheet: 15,362,611.64  
• The beginning Accounts Receivable is 0.00, so the average Accounts Receivable = (0.00 + 15,362,611.64) / 2 = 7,681,305.82  

Step 2: Identify the net sales from the income statement (Main Business Revenue): 22,876,677.56  

Step 3: Calculate the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio using the formula:  
  Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Main Business Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
  = 22,876,677.56 / 7,681,305.82  
  ≈ 2.98
